\title{Say Narration}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Use macOS text-to-speech for agent narration and announcements. Sub-agents announce themselves using different language voices speaking English. Use for multi-agent workflows where each agent has a distinct voice identity.}

\subtree{
\title{Say Narration (macOS TTS)}
\p{Use macOS text-to-speech for agent announcements and narration.}

\subtree{
\title{MANDATORY: NextColor Per Interaction}
\p{\strong{EVERY interaction MUST use NextColor with the voice name as the seed.}}

\pre{\startverb
;; Before EVERY voice announcement, compute NextColor
(def color (next-color (seed-from-string "Ava (Premium)")))
;; color determines the trit assignment: MINUS(-1), ERGODIC(0), PLUS(+1)
\stopverb}

\p{The voice name string IS the seed for deterministic color assignment. This ensures GF(3) conservation across all voice interactions.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Quality Requirements}
\p{\strong{ONLY use Enhanced or Premium quality voices. NEVER use:}}

\ul{
\li{Base/standard quality voices (no suffix)}
\li{British man voice (Daniel)}
\li{Any novelty voices (Albert, Bad News, Bells, Boing, etc.)}
}
}

